'''ABC North and West SA''' is a [[ABC Local Radio|local radio]] station based in [[Port Pirie, South Australia]], owned by the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]. Its callsign is '''5CK''' and is transmitted on [[AM broadcasting|AM]].
==History==
In 1932 5CK was a country station in South Australia and the fourth in Australia. 5CK's role was a relay transmitter of the then Australian Broadcasting Commission until 1955 when the first program aired. It was initially provided with a 6.25/7 kw [[Standard Telephones and Cables|STC]] transmitter.<ref>{{cite book|title=Australian Radio the Technical Story 1923-83|author=Winston T. Muscio|date=1984|publisher=Kangaroo Press|isbn=0-949924-82-2|page=68}}</ref>
The station and its transmitters are heard on both the AM and FM bands.
